I am using the following to sort the unique values in an array with method. The condition is Ruby's `uniq` method can't be used.

    def uniques(my_array)
    	my_array.to_a.select( |i| i != i)
    end
    puts uniques([1,5,"frog", 2,1,3,"frog"])

giving me error unexpected end-of-input.

    def uniques(my_array)

    end
    puts uniques([1,5,"frog", 2,1,3,"frog"])

How can I write a method in Ruby which takes an array of items and returns the array without any duplicates. Without using Ruby’s `uniq` method!

The result of this array `[1,5,"frog", 2,1,3,"frog"]` will be `[1,5,"frog",2,3]`

Thanks in advanced

The result of this array `[1,5,"frog", 2,1,3,"frog"]` will be `[1,5,"frog",2,3]`
